# API Design

## URL Conventions

- Use plural nouns for resources: `/leads`, not `/lead`
- Use kebab-case for multi-word paths: `/leads/{id}/reached-out`
- Version prefix when needed: `/api/v1/...`

## HTTP Methods

- `POST` for creation (returns 201)
- `GET` for reads (returns 200)
- `PUT/PATCH` for updates (returns 200)
- `DELETE` for removal (returns 204)

## Response Shape

- Success: return the Pydantic model directly (FastAPI serializes it)
- Errors: raise `HTTPException` with appropriate status code and `detail`
- List endpoints: return `list[Schema]` — add pagination if needed

## Status Codes

- 200: successful read/update
- 201: successful creation
- 400: validation error (FastAPI handles via Pydantic)
- 401: missing or invalid auth
- 403: authenticated but not authorized
- 404: resource not found
- 422: request body validation failure (FastAPI default)
